### plural executive (cont) ###

texas commissioner of the general land office
    manager of most publicly owned lands

pros and cons
    pros
        more access
        elected to position instead of appointed
    cons
        not a focus for any election
            low voter attention
        inefficient

multi-member appointed boards
    most are appointed by gov and confirmed by senate

multi-member elected boards
    examples
        railroad commission
        state board of education

sunset advisory commission (SAC)
    state agencies must justify their existence every 12 years
    legislature accepts most SAC recommendations


